Unilateral erythromelanosis follicularis faciei et colli in a young girl.
 Erythromelanosis follicularis faciei et colli is uncommon.
 Fewer than 20 cases have been reported.
 Except for one case in a woman and one case of unilateral distribution, all other reported cases have been bilateral in young male patients.
 We report the first case of unilateral distribution in a white girl.
